---
/**
 * context-engineering 0001 · Figure 3 — a real repository dwarfs the window;
 * you can show roughly ten percent.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote
 * <sup>). Lives as an .astro component so the kebab-case SVG attributes render
 * byte-for-byte. References no arrowhead markers, so it needs no inlined <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 168"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A repository dwarfs the context window; you can show roughly ten percent."
    >
        <text x="300" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >A real repo dwarfs the window</text
        >
        <!-- repo -->
        <rect x="30" y="32" width="540" height="44" rx="6" fill="#efe7f0" stroke="#111110"></rect>
        <text x="300" y="59" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Repository &nbsp;~2,000,000 tokens</text
        >
        <!-- window -->
        <rect
            x="30"
            y="92"
            width="54"
            height="40"
            rx="6"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="57" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >window</text
        >
        <text x="96" y="110" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Context window ~200,000 tokens &mdash; about 10%</text
        >
        <text x="96" y="126" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >…and the prompt, tools, history &amp; answer eat into even that.</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e"
            >Choosing WHICH 10% to show is the entire job of context engineering.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Even a "huge" window holds a fraction of a real system — and bigger isn't free: longer
        contexts cost more, run slower, and models recall the <em>middle</em> of a long window poorly.<sup
            ><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
